PumpResp — Licensing Overview
=============================

This repository contains three categories of materials:

1. Hardware designs (CAD files, schematics, wiring diagrams)
2. Software (Arduino sketches and supporting scripts)
3. Documentation (build guide, safety notes, testing procedures, text and images)

Each category is licensed under a different open-source license, as described below.
This file provides a human-readable summary. The full legal texts are included in
the LICENSES/ directory.


1. Hardware License — CERN-OHL-S v2
-----------------------------------
All hardware design files in this repository are licensed under the
CERN Open Hardware Licence Version 2 – Strongly Reciprocal (CERN-OHL-S).

You may copy, modify, and redistribute the hardware files under the terms of
CERN-OHL-S. If you distribute modified versions, you must:

- release them under the same license (strong reciprocity)
- provide the complete source for your modifications
- retain notices of authorship and license

Full license text:
https://ohwr.org/cern_ohl_s_v2.txt


2. Software License — GNU General Public License, Version 3 (GPL-3.0)
---------------------------------------------------------------------
All software in this repository (including Arduino sketches) is licensed under the
GNU General Public License, Version 3 (GPL-3.0).

Under GPL-3.0, you may:
- use, study, and modify the software
- redistribute original or modified versions

If you distribute modified versions, you must:
- release them under GPL-3.0
- provide access to the complete corresponding source code
- retain copyright and license notices

Full license text:
https://www.gnu.org/licenses/gpl-3.0.txt


3. Documentation License — CC BY 4.0
------------------------------------
All documentation in this repository is licensed under the
Creative Commons Attribution 4.0 International License (CC-BY-4.0).

You are free to share and adapt the documentation for any purpose,
provided that you give appropriate credit.

Full license text:
https://creativecommons.org/licenses/by/4.0/legalcode

4. Mixed‑Content Files
----------------------
Some files in this repository may contain multiple types of content. For example, documentation files may include hardware diagrams, wiring schematics, or software code snippets.

Each component within such mixed‑content files is licensed under its respective license:
- hardware elements → CERN‑OHL‑S v2
- software elements → GPL‑3.0
- documentation elements → CC‑BY‑4.0

When reusing or modifying mixed‑content files, please ensure that each part is handled according to the license that applies to that specific component.

5. Disclaimer of Warranty and Liability
---------------------------------------
To the maximum extent permitted by applicable law:

- The hardware, documentation, and software in this repository are provided
  "as is", without warranty of any kind.
- The author(s) make no guarantees regarding correctness, safety, fitness for a
  particular purpose, or suitability for any application.
- The author(s) shall not be liable for any damages, injuries, losses, or
  consequences arising from the use, misuse, assembly, modification, or
  distribution of this project.

By using any part of this repository, you accept full responsibility for your
own implementation, testing, and safety practices.


6. Summary
----------
Hardware:        CERN-OHL-S v2
Software:        GPL-3.0
Documentation:   CC-BY-4.0

Each component is open-source but governed by its respective license.
Please review the full license texts before using or modifying this project.
